Adj 15 meert 1697
Mons Jan Bap: masson
J'ay la vre de 11 courant avec une incluse pour don pedra garribal, adiaiart
generael & on d'affaire de mons. nostre governeur, la quelle lettre ie vous
renvoij si ioientte a chose, que ie ne veu pasmengagner, ni meme faire
conneestre a ces monsieurs, que iauroit de cognossence de vre pretence
cest un affaire que vous touche, be en la quelle ie ne vous puis pas
faireagince service, d'aut en moins achose que mons. le governeur
est a present fort smalade, & d'un mala die l'anquissente, dont il ne
queries la par, cest pour quoy il sera bien que vous viendres icy vous
mesme et parlerois a mons. pedro garribal qui vous a promis
de contenter mille florins nest en mon affaire de solliciter semblable
payement, ie suis d'opinion que sile mons. I governeur viendret de morir
vous auries bien de paine pour obtenir satisfaction cett pour quoy
le plus tost que vous sives vre pretention le millieur qu'ilsera
on m'adversi que ceux de mallines ont obtenu payement on ce pourit
addresse a eux pour scavoir par que moijen sont venu chez vous ie suis
pret pour vous rendre touttes services qui sont possibles en matiere
de negoce, le gr jespere reviver et bientoft, cependant vre pret
tion ne devrost, has estre dilaye. ie shuis att cntant vre remise
15 ditto
ier cautelse at eu touttes occasions jesuis

ick van doen hebbe sijn als volght soo ul de selve gelieft te leveren

en is ruijm meer als mijne ditferentie van mijn presentatio aen ul vras

Adij 18 meert 1697
London Walter BB. Kent
ont
sence mij last on the 14 inttant receaved yours of 26 past, with acc
of insusance abord havorth from hull sor Amstm wille is verij well,
hope that I shall well arrive, thij are to ioyne 2 ships more oft yarmoith
when you iuge de best teme to bee nothered gods shall send you patterne
& instuctions for I want allsorts of clotsh from leeds. seppect one pack more
of spanish clothes for ostend. I amongut them de light draps & affor
meart
de fme pearles, I finde my order of 11 sber last there in compleated for in
the bale N. 50 was one of 10ƒ in N. 51 are 2 suprafines No° 342 & 345 in
N2 is one & in w.3 are ƒ5 so that there is 9 pearles to the order of 14
sber last & butt 2 of all them lised to the patt. w.7 de saprafine N°. 345
in no comparison to N.7 do cost 15 st, so that I desire no such cloth, that
come soo different in coulleur for exept thij bee exactley to N:7 or better no
boddij
bobdey willooh upon then, beside I ordered butt 1 a 2 p. or 15 a 16 there
fore send non except they bee exactey to N°7 or better, whelst I hope that
voy shall procured a suffisant convoij for ostend, some say that the shipsd
for rotterdam shall begh the ostendish in sicht of ostend, & them forworth
envoyes for rott with woult not bee well, because de most danger is
upon the coust, deare ried from dunckercken, that an other esquader is
a peparinge to bee commandet bee an bart & that jtt will bee the stronge
1dea
that is itt that , so the soner the convoij come over the better en
if all thus pirates can not bes dravem awhey, wee may trade no more for
wee can not demande your goods expept de nation & deavers to secured
them over., theer: is arifinge itt can not hoult longe soo for de armies
wants monney & very considerabels sommes musth bee remitted there bee
de arrival of the lilves vliet in spaine, will cause a considerable fall
soo I shall reader a low you intrest for some time them to si you displia

hull William schanson ste no du ptrez procered the peadtul for mge accompt
my last lettre of de 14 courant was to drected to m. Henry metealf
with order to bee deliverd to you in case hee hald desined & gived over
bussene ssas m. botter wrodt to mee with now s finde confimed bee t

the 3 bales or pacles shipped tot Amst to mij orders is to content

sence mij last of 14 courant receaved yours of 2 4 past as alsoo one letter
for m. schanson the same date, with bills of loadinge of 3 bales for
Amstm, there under w 3 with cloth abord thomas haworth whith
falled out as I feared, bee cause m. metralt ait all reddy shipped 2

soult bee a great appointement itt, moust have patiens now in hopes
